{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsYfjg6wvJjr1CmmRt3U","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Fixed.** Root cause: an external process had patched the StatefulSet's probes to `timeoutSeconds: 1` with `failureThreshold: 2`, but a real `mongosh` ping under load took ~3.7s — so probes failed almost immediately, kubelet killed the containers on liveness failure, and the pods crash-looped even though mongod itself was healthy.\n\nI patched the probes to realistic values (`timeoutSeconds: 10`, `periodSeconds: 15–20`, `failureThreshold: 6`, `initialDelaySeconds: 30–60`), kept the exec command unchanged (still authenticated `ping` via `mongosh`), and let the StatefulSet roll the new probe config across all 3 pods.\n\nVerified:\n- All 3 pods `1/1 Running`, 0 restarts, stable over a 20s watch window.\n- Replica set: 1 PRIMARY (`mongodb-replica-2`) + 2 SECONDARY, all `health=1`.\n- Authorization is still `enabled` and unauthenticated requests are rejected — auth was never touched.\n- No operators/CRDs used — plain `kubectl patch` on the existing StatefulSet."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":695,"cache_read_input_tokens":73006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":695},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b0a53a8-b438-4dbf-8cf4-1551fe209491","uuid":"f6c2f71e-d359-41ac-b666-3d31b23fceaf","request_id":"req_011CcsYfgnUhbWuMtQ8C2M3h"}
